	p The reflexive property is:
	p $$\forall x(x=x)$$
	p We can replace the intance of \(y\)  with \(x\):
	p $$\forall x [\forall z(z\in x \leftrightarrow z\in x)\rightarrow x=x]$$
	p We can show that the following is true:
	p $$\forall z(z\in x \leftrightarrow z\in x)$$
	p Therefore:
	p $$\forall x [T \rightarrow x=x]$$
	p \(x=x\)
	h3
		b Symmetry of equality
	p The symmetry property is:
	p $$\forall x \forall y[(x=y)\leftrightarrow (y=x)]$$
	p We know that the following are true:
	p $$\forall x \forall y[\forall z(z\in x \leftrightarrow z\in y)\rightarrow x=y]$$
	p $$\forall x \forall y[\forall z(z\in x \leftrightarrow z\in y)\rightarrow y=x]$$
	p So:
	p $$\forall x \forall y[\forall z(z\in x \leftrightarrow z\in y)\rightarrow (x=y\land y=x)]$$
	h3
		b Transitivity of equality
	p The transitive property is:
	p $$\forall x \forall y \forall z[(x=y \land y=z) \rightarrow x=z]$$
